My response:
Hi Senator Swann,
Thank you for your response, positive steps as these are well received. More work needs to be done relative to eliminating ERIC registration database problems and any registered voter databases period. They provide an electronic window into elections that help cheaters cheat. 

Another focus will be providing a law driven canvassing requirement for counties to verify their registered voters are real and live where they say they do. This is a major problem because no one is monitoring the pool of registered voters in our counties.

Severe restrictions on mail in voting must be added, forcing the percentage allowed to be under 1%. Confidence comes from 99% of voters arriving in person with ID, to vote. Passing a law that also prohibits drop boxes and 3rd party cash donations is another area that the Assembly can make positive law improvements.

By the time the Assembly reconvenes, electronic voting equipment will be fighting words. So it's time to make them unlawful for use in elections. The Assembly needs to get behind a gold standard paper ballots with protections like 100 dollar bill. No more OfficeMax paper. This would also be a good time require the ballots are manufactured in the USA only.

Thank you for caring about Election Integrity Senator Swann. I and many others are at your disposal to help craft bills of this nature and to testify at Assembly committee hearings. 2020 has awakened the people to just how fragile the election integrity process has become and we deserve better.
Best Regards,
Michael Orr
Tellico Plains
